t level 51.  There were many higher level peeps there, a 59 wizzy, and mage, 60 enchanter, 54 Pally etc.  I found it very hard to get aggro, using my 2 weapons at the time, lammy and fungi hammer.  Neither proc, so for the first time I found myself looking for weapon upgrades that proc.  I now have a Frosty, which doesn't have the greatest proc in the world, but the proc does generate aggro.  Anyone have any suggestions for another procing weapon that will I could use along with the Frosty?  Someone suggested a sarnak warhammer, which I guess is around 9K (a little out of reach right now).  Any here have any suggestions? <p><img src=http://www.angelfire.com/rpg2/atlantacurse/final51large.txt>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/ujaraxalle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaraxalle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowls at you rdy to attack!</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#333333>(8/16/02 8:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/fguild75784frm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Taunt!</span><hr size=1> Any quest items?  Or good drops that you can get with one group?<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><img src=http://www.angelfire.com/rpg2/atlantacurse/final51large.txt>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/ueldryc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eldryc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cons Threateningly </span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#333333>(8/19/02 3:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/fguild75784frm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Taunt!</span><hr size=1> I'm not familiar with the warhammer at all and I hunt chardok a ton.  It's possible that I've missed something.  But anyway, if 9k is out of reach, then you don't have a lot of options for a fast weapon with a good aggroing proc.  Stick with frostbringer and just use a fast weapon along with it.  the lamentation or the fungi hammer are fine for that.  A guard captain's mallet is also good (11/20 +6 dex/agi +45hp, retails for 4k or maybe a little less now).  Particularly if you have a dex buff or Boon, you'll probably want frostbringer in your primary hand.  The proc taunts very well.  I wouldn't base too much of your gear right now on the fact that you had trouble keeping aggro in Kael though.  L51 is very low for a main tank there.  As you level and your offensive skills go up, you'll hit more often and for more damage, so part of the problem will take care of itself.  Your weapons are quite good for L51.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/urexxor12.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rexxor12</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowls at you rdy to attack!</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#333333>(8/20/02 2:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/fguild75784frm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Taunt!</span><hr size=1> trying giving yourself a little more time solo with the mob before calling assist.  Even at 60 I have alot of trouble keeping mobs esp. in ToV off our rogue unless i've taking about 10 good seconds of solo figthing to ensure aggro. <p>Baron Rexxor Shadowforge<BR>
